sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS number_of_students
FROM overall_performance
WHERE overall_cgpa > 8.0;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT course_id) AS total_courses
FROM student_grades
WHERE student_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Top students refer to those with the highest overall CGPA in a semester; 
Semester is a period of academic study; 
Overall CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) is a measure of a student's academic performance.
